column5: anyone have any info on Parks outpostcamps and arneey Lake  what do you think
why do you know an arbbey Lane and is she easy to hook
and it's north of Wawa not Smith Falls
thanks great info and help solopaddler

We did Parks Fly-In, went to Cam Lk/ Little Miss., we were happy with the trip but you get what you pay for, we paid $650 per guy, we had to spend a couple hours cleaning the cabin (1st goup of the year) of mouse crap, sealing window screens, and little odd jobs. Most of our gas cans had been punctured by bears and were empty. It seems to be bear city around those Chapleau Game Preserve outposts. On the whole, we were happy, we paid about 1/2 price to fish Little Miss., never met Martin but he sounded like a good guy. PM if you like  what did solopaddler have to say about the outfitter?
thanks for the info  anyone else have any info
